Using the equation in Step 10, the price of the put option is solved as follows: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{P}&=\$55\times2.71828^{-(0.02)(0.50)}+\$11.01-\$59\\[15pt]
&=\$55\times2.71828^{-(0.01)}+\$11.01-\$59\\[15pt]
&=\$55\times0.99+\$11.01-\$59\\[15pt]
&=\$54.45+\$11.01-\$59\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$6.46}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the value of the put option is $6.46.

Using the equation in Step 15, the time value of the call option is solved as follows : 

&nbsp;


$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Time Value}&=11.01-4\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$7.01}
\end{aligned}$$

Thus, the time value of the call option is $7.01.

Next, the time value of the put option is solved as follows : 

&nbsp;


$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Time Value}&=\$6.46-0\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$6.46}
\end{aligned}$$

Thus, the time value of the put option is $6.46.
